<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>How It Works - Furry Tails Photography</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="logo">
        <a href="/">
          <img src="/gallery/logo.jpeg" alt="Logo" width="40" height="40">
          Pet Photography
        </a>
      </div>
      <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger">
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </button>
      <ul class="nav-links" id="nav-links">
        <li><a href="/gallery">GALLERY</a></li>
        <li><a href="/how-it-works">SESSIONS</a></li>
        <li><a href="/prices">PRICES</a></li>
        <li><a href="/">VOUCHERS</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">ABOUT</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact">CONTACT</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="how-it-works-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <h2>Fun, simple, and a little bit chaotic (in a good way).</h2>
          <p>We keep things relaxed, playful, and focused on capturing your pet's personality. You don't need a perfectly trained pet. Curiosity, energy, and a love for treats are more than enough.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">BOOK NOW →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Three Cards Section -->
    <section class="how-it-works-cards">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cards-grid">
          <!-- Before your session -->
          <div class="how-card card-lightblue">
            <h3>Before your session</h3>
            <p>Getting ready is simple—and no, your pet doesn't need to be perfectly trained.</p>

            <div class="card-highlight">
              <p><strong>The main things? Think?</strong></p>
              <p>Just give us a heads up about your pet beforehand—a little motivation goes a long way.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card-section">
              <p><strong>YOU'RE WELCOME TO BRING</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>Favorite toys</li>
                <li>Favorite treats</li>
                <li>Anything that helps show your pet's personality</li>
              </ul>
              <p>And don't worry if your pet is a bit nervous. That's completely normal—so cool with it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- At the studio -->
          <div class="how-card card-pink">
            <h3>At the studio</h3>
            <p>Sessions take place in my home studio. Not a big commercial space—just a comfortable, well-set-up environment.</p>

            <div class="card-section">
              <p><strong>WHAT TO EXPECT</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>Professional lighting, laid back vibe</li>
                <li>Treats and playtime</li>
                <li>A home-like environment</li>
                <li>Time to let your pet warm up before we really get going</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- During the session -->
          <div class="how-card card-brown">
            <h3>During the session</h3>
            <p>We follow a natural flow that works for your pet. Some pets are confident right away, others need a moment to settle in. There we gradually build it up more.</p>

            <div class="card-section">
              <p><strong>Think:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>Jumping</li>
                <li>Sitting</li>
                <li>Catching treats</li>
              </ul>
              <p>In between we capture candid portrait moments—sitting, lying down, and those little in-between expressions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- After the session -->
    <section class="how-it-works-after">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="after-content">
          <h3>After the session</h3>
          <p>Within two weeks, you'll receive a link to your personal gallery, where you'll be able to view and choose your favorite images.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-grid">
        <div class="footer-col">
          <div class="footer-logo">
            <img src="/gallery/logo.jpeg" alt="Logo" width="30" height="30">
            <span>Pet Photography</span>
          </div>
          <p>Capturing the joy and personality of your beloved pets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <h4>QUICK LINKS</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/gallery">Gallery</a></li>
            <li><a href="/how-it-works">Sessions</a></li>
            <li><a href="/prices">Prices</a></li>
            <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <h4>LET'S CONNECT</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://instagram.com">Instagram</a></li>
            <li><a href="tel:+1234567890">(123) 456-7890</a></li>
            <li><a href="mailto:hello@furrytails.com">Email</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-col">
          <a href="/contact" class="footer-cta">BOOK A SESSION</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-bottom">
        <p>&copy; 2026 Furry Tails Pet Photography. All rights reserved.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const hamburger = document.getElementById('hamburger');
    const navLinks = document.getElementById('nav-links');

    hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => {
      hamburger.classList.toggle('active');
      navLinks.style.display = navLinks.style.display === 'flex' ? 'none' : 'flex';
    });

    navLinks.querySelectorAll('a').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        hamburger.classList.remove('active');
        navLinks.style.display = 'none';
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
